OL,3,CTV-related anniversaries for 20 APR
OL,4,CCHANNELS
OL,5,
OL,6,CG1964FBBC Two was expected to launch
OL,7,Fat 7.20pm. However, a serious power
OL,8,Ffailure at Battersea Power Station
OL,9,Fknocked out the power supply to BBC
OL,10,FTelevision Centre. BBC One was kept on
OL,11,Fthe air via facilities at Alexandra
OL,12,FPalace. Other than occasional news
OL,13,Fupdates on BBC Two that evening, where
OL,14,Fpresenter Gerald Priestland explained
OL,15,Fthe power issues, no other programmes
OL,16,Fwere broadcast on BBC Two that day. The
OL,17,Ffirst official programme on BBC Two was
OL,18,FPlay School at 11am the next day.
